1

00:00:01,149  -->  00:00:05,660
So you saw that you can't add categorical explanatory variables into

2

00:00:05,660  -->  00:00:09,679
your X matrix as nicely as you were able to add quantitative variables.

3

00:00:09,679  -->  00:00:14,554
Instead of adding columns like this into your X matrix with values such as A,

4

00:00:14,554  -->  00:00:16,399
B, and C for the neighborhood,

5

00:00:16,399  -->  00:00:19,759
we end up creating what are known as dummy variables.

6

00:00:19,760  -->  00:00:22,505
There are a few different ways to encode dummy variables.

7

00:00:22,504  -->  00:00:28,254
But most commonly used are the ones where you encode one and zero.

8

00:00:28,254  -->  00:00:33,524
The way this works is we create a column for each value in this column.

9

00:00:33,524  -->  00:00:35,244
And for each column,

10

00:00:35,244  -->  00:00:40,344
there's a one if the value exists in the column and a zero otherwise.

11

00:00:40,344  -->  00:00:45,100
So the column we would create for the A values would look like this.

12

00:00:45,100  -->  00:00:48,145
Then, when we want to create a column for the B values,

13

00:00:48,145  -->  00:00:49,615
it would look like this.

14

00:00:49,615  -->  00:00:53,920
And finally, the last column for C would look like this.

15

00:00:53,920  -->  00:00:55,690
You will want to do this for each of

16

00:00:55,689  -->  00:00:58,859
the categorical variables that you want to add in your data set.

17

00:00:58,859  -->  00:01:02,695
Because this last column can be inferred from the earlier two columns,

18

00:01:02,695  -->  00:01:05,245
as the one values are only in the rows

19

00:01:05,245  -->  00:01:08,200
that didn't have ones in one of these other columns,

20

00:01:08,200  -->  00:01:12,219
we actually end up choosing to drop this column.

21

00:01:12,219  -->  00:01:15,875
Which one you drop doesn't really matter too much.

22

00:01:15,875  -->  00:01:17,215
In the next concept,

23

00:01:17,215  -->  00:01:20,750
you will see the mathematical reasoning for dropping a column.

24

00:01:20,750  -->  00:01:24,280
And then, the screencast will show you how this works in practice.
